“building”  means,  in  relation  to  Part  II,  any  building  used  for 
the housing of employees and includes a nursery and a community 
hall;

(b)  as  respects  parents,  the  parents  of  an  illegitimate  child, 
and  any  person  by  whom  the  employee  was  adopted  in 
accordance  with  any  written  law  relating  to  adoption;

“Medical  Officer”  means  a  registered  medical  practitioner 
who  is  employed  in  a  medical  capacity  by  the  Federal  or  State 
Government;

“place  of  employment”  means  a  place  where  work  is  carried 
on  by  or  on  behalf  of  or  for  an  employer  and  shall  include  any 
place  in  which  employees  are  housed  by  an  employer;

“resident manager”, in relation to an estate, means any employer 
or agent of an employer who resides on, or is in immediate charge 
of,  the  estate  in  which  the  employees  are  employed;

(c)  to  ensure  that  the  buildings  are  kept  in  a  good  state  of 
repair  and  painted  to  present  a  satisfactory  appearance; 
and

Provided  that  the  Director  General  may,  if  he  is  satisfied  in 
any  case  that  it  is  impracticable  to  provide  piped  water  supply 
for  each  house,  approve  any  other  means  of  water  supply:

(a)  the  area  surrounding  the  employees’  housing  is  kept  
clear  of  undergrowth  and  maintained  in  a  clean  and 
sanitary  condition;

“accommodation” means any permanent or temporary building 
or  structure  including  any  house,  hut,  shed  or  roofed  enclosure 
used  for  the  purpose  of  human  habitation;

(b)   to  direct  employer  or  centralized  accommodation  
provider  to  submit  any  information  and  documents 
relating  to  an  employee’s  accommodation;

(c)   to  issue  any  directions  to  an  employer  or  a  centralized 
accommodation provider to provide any other amenities 
relating  to  an  accommodation;

(d)   to ensure that the electrical wiring systems comply with 
safety  requirements  in  accordance  with  the  relevant 
written  laws;

(ab)   to prescribe any class, category or description of employees 
that  is  required  to  be  provided  with  accommodation 
under  Part  IIIa;

(c)  copy  or  make  extracts  from  such  record,  contract  of 
service,  book  of  account  of  wages,  register  and  any 
other  document  referred  to  in  paragraph  (b);
